creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 127 by Various.

This is a collection of 21 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for December 2013.
This collection includes the following:
An Account Of The Greatest English Poets by Joseph Addison Barter by Sara Teasdale The Calf Path by Sam Walter Foss The Complaint of the Fair Helm-maker Grown Old by François Villon Dulce Et Decorum Est by Wilfred Owen Free Will by Alice Meynell He Couldn’t Say No by M. E. B. He Leadeth Me by Henry H. Barry I Serve a Mistress by Anthony Munday The Lake Isle of Innisfree by William Butler Yeats Luna by Gerald Miller Men Improve with the Years by William Butler Yeats No worst, there is none by Gerard Manley Hopkins A Nocturnall Upon St. Lucies Day, Being the Shortest Day by John Donne The One Certainty by Christina Rossetti Psalm 23: The Lord My Pasture Shall Prepare by Joseph Addison Saltbush Bill on the Patriarchs by Andrew Barton "Banjo" Paterson The Silence by John Gould Fletcher A Sonnet of the Moon by Charles Best The Spacious Firmament on High by Joseph Addison To My Wife by Conrad Aiken

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

M4B Format Available
